---
title: Beef & Greek Salad Lettuce Wraps topped with Feta
description: There’s just something so satisfying about a lettuce wrap. The crisp romaine crunch, the perfectly cradled filling, and that satisfied-but-not-stuffed feeling after dinner. This version features ground turkey seasoned with Turkish-inspired spices, garlic, and soy sauce, then topped with fresh cucumber, tomato, red onion, feta, and a sweet and herby Greek vinaigrette. Prepare to start raving about lettuce wraps as much as we do!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/turkey-greek-salad-lettuce-wraps-29c21c5c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64dbd22f3466802bb5e731de.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 49 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 17 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1290 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beef-and-greek-salad-lettuce-wraps-6570d83cddd2bdfd232c840b
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); slice crosswise into ½-inch pieces. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Halve, peel, and finely chop @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and finely chopped). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(root end trimmed and leaves separated); separate leaves.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, 2 TBSP onion (4 TBSP for 4 servings; you'll use the rest later), and @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%oz}. Toss to coat.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @Turkish spice blend{1%tbsp}, garlic, and half the @soy sauce{2%tbsp} (all for 4 servings). Cook, breaking meat up into pieces, until beef is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with salt and @pepper{} to taste.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Divide lettuce between #plates{}. Fill with beef and salad. Spoon any remaining vinaigrette from bowl over top. Garnish wraps with @feta cheese{½%cup} and serve.

> TIP: Stir in a splash of water near the end of cooking to make sure your turkey is nice and saucy!

> Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Cook through this step as instructed, swapping in chicken (no need to break up into pieces!) or beef for turkey.